===Etymology===
:from the Middle English ''girle'' or ''gerle'', which means a young person, from the Low German ''gör'' and ''göre'', a young male or a young female, respectively.

===Noun===
''Plural'': girls.
#a female child or young person (a young male is a ''[[boy]]'').
#any ''[[woman]]'', regardless of age (calling a grown ''[[woman]]'' a ''girl'' may be considered either  a compliment or an insult, depending on context and sensibilities.)
#A female servant.  Maid.

